cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper discusses communication approaches in robot swarms, which is a typical topic in multiagent systems research.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on experiments performed with microrobots.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses hardware implementation aspects of communication mechanisms in robot swarms.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses communication approaches for large-scale systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper only briefly mentions epidemic algorithms as one of the communication approaches.
